properties.areaDesc: North Snowy Range Foothills; South Laramie Range Foothills; South Laramie Range; Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 13 at 1:02PM MST until February 15 at 6:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 40 to 45 mph with gusts up to 70 mph expected.
Blowing snow.

* WHERE...Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County,
North Snowy Range Foothills, South Laramie Range and South
Laramie Range Foothills Counties.

* WHEN...From 8 AM Friday to 6 PM MST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...High risk for blowovers. Travel will be difficult for
lightweight, high profile vehicles and campers. Blowing snow
will significantly reduce visibility and made roads slick.
properties.instruction:
Go to wyoroad.info or call 5 1 1 for the latest road conditions
and closures in Wyoming.

NWSheadline: HIGH WINDS AND BLOWING SNOW WILL IMPACT TRAVEL FRIDAY AND SATURDAY
